<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// When the shift size is not a multiple of the word size, then we have</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="596"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// a tricky situation where each word in succession needs to extract some</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// of the bits from the next word and or them into this word while</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="598"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// shifting this word to make room for the new bits.  This has to be done</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00599" /><CodeLine lineNumber="599"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for every word in the array.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="600"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="601"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Since we&#39;re shifting each word right, some bits will fall off the end</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="602"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// of each word to the right, and empty space will be created on the left.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="603"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The final word in the array will lose bits permanently, so starting at</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00604" /><CodeLine lineNumber="604"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the beginning, work forwards shifting each word to the right, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00605" /><CodeLine lineNumber="605"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// OR&#39;ing in the bits from the end of the next word to the beginning of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00606" /><CodeLine lineNumber="606"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the current word.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00607" /><CodeLine lineNumber="607"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00608" /><CodeLine lineNumber="608"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Example:</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00610" /><CodeLine lineNumber="610"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   by 4 bits.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00611" /><CodeLine lineNumber="611"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Step 1: Word&#91;0&#93; &gt;&gt;= 4           ; 180079837</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00644" /><CodeLine lineNumber="644"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// When the shift size is not a multiple of the word size, then we have</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00650" /><CodeLine lineNumber="650"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00651" /><CodeLine lineNumber="651"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Since we&#39;re shifting each word left, some bits will fall off the end</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00653" /><CodeLine lineNumber="653"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The first word in the array will lose bits permanently, so starting at</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00694" /><CodeLine lineNumber="694"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Portable bit mask operations.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00695" /><CodeLine lineNumber="695"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===--------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00696" /><CodeLine lineNumber="696"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00697" /><CodeLine lineNumber="697"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// These methods all operate on arrays of uint32&#95;t, each holding 32 bits. The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00698" /><CodeLine lineNumber="698"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// fixed word size makes it easier to work with literal bit vector constants</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00699" /><CodeLine lineNumber="699"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// in portable code.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00700" /><CodeLine lineNumber="700"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00701" /><CodeLine lineNumber="701"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The LSB in each word is the lowest numbered bit.  The size of a portable</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00702" /><CodeLine lineNumber="702"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// bit mask is always a whole multiple of 32 bits.  If no bit mask size is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00703" /><CodeLine lineNumber="703"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// given, the bit mask is assumed to cover the entire BitVector.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00704" /><CodeLine lineNumber="704"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00705" /><CodeLine lineNumber="705"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// setBitsInMask - Add &#39;1&#39; bits from Mask to this vector. Don&#39;t resize.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00706" /><CodeLine lineNumber="706"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// This computes &quot;&#42;this |= Mask&quot;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00707" /><CodeLine lineNumber="707" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/bitvector/#a70087136d08e0945efab3c947b5e89c7"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/bitvector/#a70087136d08e0945efab3c947b5e89c7">setBitsInMask</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> uint32&#95;t &#42;Mask, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> MaskWords = ~0u) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00708" /><CodeLine lineNumber="708"><span class="doxyHighlight">    applyMask&lt;true, false&gt;(Mask, MaskWords);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00709" /><CodeLine lineNumber="709"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00710" /><CodeLine lineNumber="710"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00711" /><CodeLine lineNumber="711"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// clearBitsInMask - Clear any bits in this vector that are set in Mask.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00712" /><CodeLine lineNumber="712"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Don&#39;t resize. This computes &quot;&#42;this &amp;= ~Mask&quot;.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00717" /><CodeLine lineNumber="717"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// setBitsNotInMask - Add a bit to this vector for every &#39;0&#39; bit in Mask.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00722" /><CodeLine lineNumber="722"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00723" /><CodeLine lineNumber="723"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// clearBitsNotInMask - Clear a bit in this vector for every &#39;0&#39; bit in Mask.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00724" /><CodeLine lineNumber="724"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Don&#39;t resize.  This computes &quot;&#42;this &amp;= Mask&quot;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00725" /><CodeLine lineNumber="725" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/bitvector/#a51711ad960e294ac064a578ebfae0de7"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/bitvector/#a51711ad960e294ac064a578ebfae0de7">clearBitsNotInMask</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> uint32&#95;t &#42;Mask, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> MaskWords = ~0u) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00727" /><CodeLine lineNumber="727"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00728" /><CodeLine lineNumber="728"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00729" /><CodeLine lineNumber="729"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">private</span><span class="doxyHighlight">:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00730" /><CodeLine lineNumber="730"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Perform a logical left shift of \\p Count words by moving everything</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00731" /><CodeLine lineNumber="731"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// \\p Count words to the right in memory.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00732" /><CodeLine lineNumber="732"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00733" /><CodeLine lineNumber="733"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// While confusing, words are stored from least significant at Bits&#91;0&#93; to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00734" /><CodeLine lineNumber="734"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// most significant at Bits&#91;NumWords-1&#93;.  A logical shift left, however,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00735" /><CodeLine lineNumber="735"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// moves the current least significant bit to a higher logical index, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00736" /><CodeLine lineNumber="736"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// fills the previous least significant bits with 0  Thus, we actually</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00737" /><CodeLine lineNumber="737"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// need to move the bytes of the memory to the right, not to the left.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00738" /><CodeLine lineNumber="738"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Example:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00739" /><CodeLine lineNumber="739"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   Words = &#91;0xBBBBAAAA, 0xDDDDFFFF, 0x00000000, 0xDDDD0000&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00740" /><CodeLine lineNumber="740"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// represents a BitVector where 3149638314 contain the least significant</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00741" /><CodeLine lineNumber="741"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// bits.  So if we want to shift the BitVector left by 2 words, we need</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00742" /><CodeLine lineNumber="742"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// to turn this into 0 0 3149638314 3722313727 by using a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00743" /><CodeLine lineNumber="743"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// memmove which moves right, not left.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00744" /><CodeLine lineNumber="744"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> wordShl(uint32&#95;t <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a845e08be4b0320d66901a66b0c0e9509">Count</a>) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00745" /><CodeLine lineNumber="745"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a845e08be4b0320d66901a66b0c0e9509">Count</a> == 0)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00746" /><CodeLine lineNumber="746"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00747" /><CodeLine lineNumber="747"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00748" /><CodeLine lineNumber="748"><span class="doxyHighlight">    uint32&#95;t NumWords = Bits.size();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00749" /><CodeLine lineNumber="749"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00750" /><CodeLine lineNumber="750"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Since we always move Word-sized chunks of data with src and dest both</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00751" /><CodeLine lineNumber="751"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// aligned to a word-boundary, we don&#39;t need to worry about endianness</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00752" /><CodeLine lineNumber="752"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// here.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><span class="doxyHighlight">    std::copy(Bits.begin(), Bits.begin() + NumWords - <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a845e08be4b0320d66901a66b0c0e9509">Count</a>,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"><span class="doxyHighlight">              Bits.begin() + <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a845e08be4b0320d66901a66b0c0e9509">Count</a>);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00755" /><CodeLine lineNumber="755"><span class="doxyHighlight">    std::fill(Bits.begin(), Bits.begin() + <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a845e08be4b0320d66901a66b0c0e9509">Count</a>, 0);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00756" /><CodeLine lineNumber="756"><span class="doxyHighlight">    clear&#95;unused&#95;bits();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00757" /><CodeLine lineNumber="757"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00758" /><CodeLine lineNumber="758"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00759" /><CodeLine lineNumber="759"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Perform a logical right shift of \\p Count words by moving those</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00760" /><CodeLine lineNumber="760"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// words to the left in memory.  See wordShl for more information.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00761" /><CodeLine lineNumber="761"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00762" /><CodeLine lineNumber="762"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> wordShr(uint32&#95;t <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a845e08be4b0320d66901a66b0c0e9509">Count</a>) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00763" /><CodeLine lineNumber="763"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a845e08be4b0320d66901a66b0c0e9509">Count</a> == 0)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00764" /><CodeLine lineNumber="764"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00765" /><CodeLine lineNumber="765"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00766" /><CodeLine lineNumber="766"><span class="doxyHighlight">    uint32&#95;t NumWords = Bits.size();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00767" /><CodeLine lineNumber="767"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00768" /><CodeLine lineNumber="768"><span class="doxyHighlight">    std::copy(Bits.begin() + <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a845e08be4b0320d66901a66b0c0e9509">Count</a>, Bits.begin() + NumWords, Bits.begin());</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00769" /><CodeLine lineNumber="769"><span class="doxyHighlight">    std::fill(Bits.begin() + NumWords - <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a845e08be4b0320d66901a66b0c0e9509">Count</a>, Bits.begin() + NumWords, 0);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00770" /><CodeLine lineNumber="770"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00771" /><CodeLine lineNumber="771"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00772" /><CodeLine lineNumber="772"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">int</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> next&#95;unset&#95;in&#95;word(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">int</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> WordIndex, BitWord Word)</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword"> const </span><span class="doxyHighlight">&#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00773" /><CodeLine lineNumber="773"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/ms-demangle/#afb795990ffc0cb7321e7d1eacc246324a8eea62084ca7e541d918e823422bd82e">Result</a> = WordIndex &#42; BITWORD&#95;SIZE + <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a239abca11deebf2731206dd41cf43c0e">llvm::countr&#95;one</a>(Word);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00775" /><CodeLine lineNumber="775"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00776" /><CodeLine lineNumber="776"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00777" /><CodeLine lineNumber="777"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> NumBitWords(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> S)</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword"> const </span><span class="doxyHighlight">&#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00778" /><CodeLine lineNumber="778"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (S + BITWORD&#95;SIZE-1) / BITWORD&#95;SIZE;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00779" /><CodeLine lineNumber="779"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00780" /><CodeLine lineNumber="780"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00781" /><CodeLine lineNumber="781"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Set the unused bits in the high words.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00782" /><CodeLine lineNumber="782"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> set&#95;unused&#95;bits(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> t = </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">true</span><span class="doxyHighlight">) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00783" /><CodeLine lineNumber="783"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  Then set any stray high bits of the last used word.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00784" /><CodeLine lineNumber="784"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> ExtraBits = Size % BITWORD&#95;SIZE) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00785" /><CodeLine lineNumber="785"><span class="doxyHighlight">      BitWord ExtraBitMask = ~BitWord(0) &lt;&lt; ExtraBits;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00786" /><CodeLine lineNumber="786"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (t)</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00790" /><CodeLine lineNumber="790"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00796" /><CodeLine lineNumber="796"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00797" /><CodeLine lineNumber="797"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00798" /><CodeLine lineNumber="798"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> init&#95;words(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> t) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00800" /><CodeLine lineNumber="800"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00802" /><CodeLine lineNumber="802"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">template</span><span class="doxyHighlight">&lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> AddBits, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> InvertMask&gt;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00804" /><CodeLine lineNumber="804"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static&#95;assert</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(BITWORD&#95;SIZE % 32 == 0, </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;Unsupported BitWord size.&quot;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00805" /><CodeLine lineNumber="805"><span class="doxyHighlight">    MaskWords = std::min(MaskWords, (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/bitvector/#abf86e1383aec181a5a2d9967eb8070fd">size</a>() + 31) / 32);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00806" /><CodeLine lineNumber="806"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Scale = BITWORD&#95;SIZE / 32;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00807" /><CodeLine lineNumber="807"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> i;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00808" /><CodeLine lineNumber="808"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (i = 0; MaskWords &gt;= Scale; ++i, MaskWords -= Scale) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00809" /><CodeLine lineNumber="809"><span class="doxyHighlight">      BitWord BW = Bits&#91;i&#93;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00810" /><CodeLine lineNumber="810"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This inner loop should unroll completely when BITWORD&#95;SIZE &gt; 32</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00811" /><CodeLine lineNumber="811"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> b = 0; <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/m68k/#ab3a288f2953d8eca3e363959fc2cf38ea92eb5ffee6ae2fec3ad71c777531578f">b</a> != BITWORD&#95;SIZE; <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/m68k/#ab3a288f2953d8eca3e363959fc2cf38ea92eb5ffee6ae2fec3ad71c777531578f">b</a> += 32) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00813" /><CodeLine lineNumber="813"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (InvertMask) <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/arm/#ac2456158e5acb44477d8ecfa2d04dbdea69691c7bdcc3ce6d5d8a1361f22d04ac">M</a> = ~M;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00814" /><CodeLine lineNumber="814"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (AddBits) BW |=   BitWord(M) &lt;&lt; <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/m68k/#ab3a288f2953d8eca3e363959fc2cf38ea92eb5ffee6ae2fec3ad71c777531578f">b</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00815" /><CodeLine lineNumber="815"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span><span class="doxyHighlight">         BW &amp;= ~(BitWord(M) &lt;&lt; <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/m68k/#ab3a288f2953d8eca3e363959fc2cf38ea92eb5ffee6ae2fec3ad71c777531578f">b</a>);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00818" /><CodeLine lineNumber="818"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00819" /><CodeLine lineNumber="819"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> b = 0; MaskWords; <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/m68k/#ab3a288f2953d8eca3e363959fc2cf38ea92eb5ffee6ae2fec3ad71c777531578f">b</a> += 32, --MaskWords) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00820" /><CodeLine lineNumber="820"><span class="doxyHighlight">      uint32&#95;t <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/arm/#ac2456158e5acb44477d8ecfa2d04dbdea69691c7bdcc3ce6d5d8a1361f22d04ac">M</a> = &#42;<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/bitmaskenumdetail/#a4562904154aff9698a612bc7f6086a4c">Mask</a>++;</span></CodeLine>
